      "text": [
        " : «كَانَ اَلنَّاسُ يُقَلِّدُونَ اَلْغَنَمَ وَ اَلْبَقَرَ وَ إِنَّمَا تَرَكَهُ اَلنَّاسُ حَدِيثاً وَ يُقَلِّدُونَ بِخَيْطٍ أَوْ بِسَيْرٍ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2571 - Hariz narrated from Zurara, from Abu Ja'far (as), who said:\n\"People used to adorn sheep and cattle with garlands, but they have recently abandoned this practice. They would garland them with a string or a leather strap.\""
        ]
      }
